These are a few of the tools and services that have most resently been used here:


Windows 10, Ubuntu 16.04, Android, and iOS;


Notepad++, Gedit, Atom, and a little Vi/Vim
( Thinking to use Vim more. VS Code is neat 😜 );


WordPress, Ghost, and flat files;


Photoshop, Illustrator, GIMP, Inkscape, and Blender;


LibreOffice, Google Docs, and Trello;


GitHub, Bitbucket, and DigitalOcean.


Once in a while will jump in AWS, but not so much resently. Would really like to use containers more. There are so many good hosting and the like companies out there, and so many of them are good- it can be difficult to choose one, but mostly out of the warm techno fuzzies.

Used to use the like of 3d Studio Max, Maya, Modo, ZBrush, After Effects, and absolutely loved Houdini; along with Quake, Unreal, and lots of other engines.

"}]],"sections":[[10,0]]}
posts.html:
These are a few of the tools and services that have most resently been used here:


Windows 10, Ubuntu 16.04, Android, and iOS;


Notepad++, Gedit, Atom, and a little Vi/Vim
( Thinking to use Vim more. VS Code is neat 😜 );


WordPress, Ghost, and flat files;


Photoshop, Illustrator, GIMP, Inkscape, and Blender;


LibreOffice, Google Docs, and Trello;


GitHub, Bitbucket, and DigitalOcean.


Once in a while will jump in AWS, but not so much resently. Would really like to use containers more. There are so many good hosting and the like companies out there, and so many of them are good- it can be difficult to choose one, but mostly out of the warm techno fuzzies.

Used to use the like of 3d Studio Max, Maya, Modo, ZBrush, After Effects, and absolutely loved Houdini; along with Quake, Unreal, and lots of other engines.
